PART I — OPEN SOURCE COMPONENTS
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

ARKLinux is an Arch Linux–based distribution.  The base operating system,
kernel, system libraries, and third-party packages are distributed under their
respective upstream licenses (GPL-2.0, GPL-3.0, MIT, LGPL-2.1, BSD-2-Clause,
Apache-2.0, and others).  A machine-readable Software Bill of Materials (SBOM)
in SPDX format is generated for every official release and attached to the
corresponding GitHub Release as "arklinux-<version>-sbom.spdx.json".  The SBOM
is the authoritative record of all included components and their licenses.

Source code for all GPL-licensed components is available via the upstream Arch
Linux Archive snapshot pinned in archiso/pacman.conf and build/lock/packages.lock
at the exact date stamped in each release.

