PART III — ARK CONCEPT AND BRANDING (Proprietary)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

The "A.R.K." concept, the ARKLinux name, the ARKLinux logo (if any), the
CPA/MDS/SAL/VerifiedClaim JSON schemas, and the ARK operator identity model
are proprietary to Superman08091992 and are NOT licensed for redistribution or
derivative branding without explicit written permission.

You MAY:
  • Run ARKLinux for personal, educational, or internal organizational use.
  • Study the schemas and concept documentation.
  • Fork the build infrastructure (Part II above) under the MIT terms, provided
    you remove ARKLinux branding and rename the resulting distribution.

You MAY NOT:
  • Distribute a modified ISO or package set under the "ARKLinux" or "A.R.K."
    name without written permission.
  • Use the ARK logo or trade dress in any derivative work.
  • Claim official endorsement or certification from the ARKLinux project.

