PART IV — RELEASE INTEGRITY AND SUPPLY-CHAIN TERMS
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Every official ARKLinux release is signed with cosign/sigstore and/or a project
GPG key.  Release artifacts attached to https://github.com/Superman08091992/ARKlinux
include:

  • ISO image (*.iso)
  • SHA-256 checksum manifest (SHA256SUMS)
  • Cosign bundle or GPG signature (*.bundle / *.sig)
  • SPDX SBOM (*.spdx.json)
  • SLSA-style provenance attestation (*.intoto.jsonl)

End users SHOULD verify the signature and checksum before booting or installing.
Verification instructions are in docs/BUILDING.md.

Unofficial builds (ISOs not produced by the GitHub Actions workflow in
.github/workflows/build-release.yml and not signed by the project key) are NOT
endorsed and carry no warranty.

